I wanted to keep this as self-contained as possible, since not all our documentation is public yet and documentation links also may change/move around.  And this isn't really supposed to be used as documentation for creating a service's init script, I also wanted to explicitly call this out with an example, as several people have already asked me about SELinux denials seen during their development, which wound up being due to running the program directly from a shell rather than through init.

